<br>
1.) if they suck (individually), they'll have to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> improve</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> themselves or find no groups. Lets face it, we've all had experiences with bad healers in general. But unfortunately with some cases, we've had to take that crappy cleric over a decent druid or shaman because of the heal spells a cleric gets. Now you can have that druid or shaman bud you liked a lot over that crappy cleric. <br>
<br>
2.) Backup. Another fact is, you can't always get a mezzer, and sometimes you want a lot of pulls without having to worry about the cleric's mana. The cleric gets low on mana, well damn...guess we have to wait because the druid/shaman can't heal well enough. But after this...low on mana? no prob, that other priest class will take over while you med <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . for the most part a druid or shaman will be there WITH a cleric as a support because clerics basically have a lot of the healing on their shoulders alone at high levels. I learned how to heal as I do even with Chloroblast because I grouped in OT and DL with chain pulling buds at the time...and my competition in healing was a cleric, with all those great heals. I had to learn utilize what i had efficiently for the times the cleric had to med. Now sometimes I'm the guildies' mock-cleric <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
3.) Buffs. Face it, cleric skin buffs are just really damn good. Shaman? yeah right...are YOU going to turn down those shaman buffs and slows to make him the main healer? doubtful. Your shaman will end up having to cannibalize themselves to hell doing the whole role. <br>
<br>
4.) Efficiency. Shamans and druids don't get those great other heals that clerics get. I'd trade in my epic for a group heal...the celestial heals are just awesome too. Lets compare...<br>
<br>
Celestial Elixir (cleric)- heals up to 1000 hitpoints over a 24 second period. Bought in Firiona Vie at level 59.<br>
<br>
Nature's Recovery (druid) - Regeneration for 900 Hit Points over 3 minutes. Rare drop spell at level 60. <br>
<br>
Torpor (Shaman) - Recover 1200 hitpoints of health in 24 seconds. The downside is the target has its movement speed reduced by 30% whilst it is in effect (snare), and also attacks at a slower rate (30%). Rare drop spell at level 60. Not sure if it even works on anyone outside your group because of the negative effects.<br>
<br>
<br>
The only major issue i see with clerics having problem with soloing, is that most might not know how to. They've been playing a group majority class for the longest time, its kind of hard to take it to a solo act. Clerics have waaaaay better ac than us druids though, so dont give us the cry about meleeing, we really can't even fight half of our own pulls one on one unless its running away. <br>
<br>
What about a cheap strength/attack debuff itself for clerics...a bit like the ones Shadowknights get, but allowable because they don't steal it, they don't get the bonus...just minus some str/atk from the enemy. <br>
<br>
<br>
I'm looking forward to it...it means more raids, and more groups. Especially guildie groups, because now my cleric buds can play those melee alts or even melee themselves if they want <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
I'll handle the heals <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
