<br>
VI gets rid of all EQ classes.<br>
VI makes one super god class.<br>
Everyones character is changed to that god class.<br>
God class can CH, DT, HT, FD, Snare, REZ, nuke.<br>
Everyone gets bored.<br>
Everyone quits.<br>
<br>
Easy enough solution?<br>
<br>
Class balancing is in the eye of the beholder. Druids get something one class complains. Shadowknights get something Paladins complain. Ranger get something... no one cares.<br>
<br>
I am a druid. I looked at this CH they had on test and thought wow that would be really nice in raids. I spend most of my time raiding. My guild is heavy on druids... 4 active 60's and most of the time were at all the raids... 2 druids with new ch = 1 cleric... thats 2 more clerics...<br>
Exp wise... well it just adds to the slippery slope of class balancing.<br>
<br>
I say give everyone 1 new spell and be done with it, no more class balancing. And stop letting Aego overwrite POTG... <br>
<br>
